==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Surplice
<hw>Sur"plice</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>surplis</ets>, OF. <ets>surpeiz</ets>, LL.
<ets>superpellicium</ets>; <ets>super</ets> over + <ets>pellicium</ets>,
<ets>pelliceum</ets>, a robe of fur, L. <ets>pellicius</ets> made of
skins. See <er>Pelisse</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A white
garment worn over another dress by the clergy of the Roman Catholic,
Episcopal, and certain other churches, in some of their
ministrations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Surplice fees</b></col> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld>, <cd>fees paid
to the English clergy for occasional duties.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Surpliced</ent>⟦br⟧
